TCP Client for Android
======================
Open this project in Android Studio!
Get it from here: http://developer.android.com/sdk/installing/studio.html

Instructions:
- Run the AndroidTCPServer on your computer
- Edit the TcpClient.java file in Android Studio according to your computers IP address (public static final String SERVER_IP = "192.168.1.67";) - You can find your computers IP address by typing 'ipconfig' in a command line on windows (or 'ifconfig' in linux terminal)
- Build the project and emulate
- Enjoy!

Full credit to Laura Suciu
http://myandroidsolutions.blogspot.ro/2013/03/android-tcp-connection-enhanced.html
